> > NAME
> >        strsep - extract token from string
> > [...]
> > RETURN VALUE
> >        The strsep() function returns a pointer to the  token,  or
> >        NULL if delim is not found in stringp.
> > 
> > If strsep returns NULL, and you dereference it -> Oops.
